mLogEntryCount.name: mLogEntryCount
mLogEntryCount.description: The number of entries currently in the message log buffer.

mLogNewMessageTrapEnable.name: mLogNewMessageTrapEnable
mLogNewMessageTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables the generation of mLogNewMessage Traps of a priority numerically equal or lower than the value of this variable.

mLogBuffer.name: mLogBuffer
mLogBuffer.description: A list of message log entries.

mLogMessage.name: mLogMessage
mLogMessage.description: An entry in the message log. Entries are indexed by counting integers. Since the earliest messages are dropped from the log when it overflows, the first row in the table is not necessarily row 1. Therefore, a Get-Next request should be issued to determine the index of the first row.

mLogTimeStamp.name: mLogTimeStamp
mLogTimeStamp.description: The time the message was generated, measured in number of ticks since the device started.

mLogPriority.name: mLogPriority
mLogPriority.description: The priority of the log message. This field is for future use. All messages are currently logged at priority 'notice'

mLogMessageText.name: mLogMessageText
mLogMessageText.description: The text of the log message.

mLogTimeOfDay.name: mLogTimeOfDay
mLogTimeOfDay.description: The time of day at which the message is logged. This is expressed in seconds.

sccTable.name: sccTable
sccTable.description: Each row of this table describes a (Zilog) 8530 Serial Communications Controller.

sccEntry.name: sccEntry
sccEntry.description: The object type of the rows in sccTable. If an interface does not have an SCC there will not be a row in the table for that interface's value of ifIndex.

sccInterrupts.name: sccInterrupts
sccInterrupts.description: Number of receive interrupts generated by the SCC.

sccAborts.name: sccAborts
sccAborts.description: The number of abort interrupts generated by the SCC.

sccSpuriousInts.name: sccSpuriousInts
sccSpuriousInts.description: The number of spurious interrupts generated by the SCC.

sccDeferTimeouts.name: sccDeferTimeouts
sccDeferTimeouts.description: Total number of defer timeouts. A defer timeout is the condition in which the line did not become idle for one and a half packet times, while the SCC was waiting to transmit, forcing a reset of the receiver. This event could indicate a misbehaving localtalk device.

bufferSize.name: bufferSize
bufferSize.description: The size of the buffers in the buffer pool. All buffers are the same size.

bufferAvail.name: bufferAvail
bufferAvail.description: The total number of buffers initialized. This does not indicate the number of currently free buffers. Rather it is the total number of buffers which were created and made free at boot time.

bufferDrops.name: bufferDrops
bufferDrops.description: The total number of times that a buffer was requested when none was available.

bufferTypeTable.name: bufferTypeTable
bufferTypeTable.description: Each row of this table describes statistics on buffers allocated for a specific purpose. The sum of bufferTypeCount for all rows should always equal the bufferAvail count.

bufferTypeEntry.name: bufferTypeEntry
bufferTypeEntry.description: The object type of the rows in bufferTypeTable.

bufferTypeIndex.name: bufferTypeIndex
bufferTypeIndex.description: The enumeration of each buffer type row.

bufferTypeCount.name: bufferTypeCount
bufferTypeCount.description: The number of buffers of the type which is described by the value of bufferTypeType for this row.

bufferTypeDrops.name: bufferTypeDrops
bufferTypeDrops.description: The number of requests for buffers this type which were not fulfilled because no free buffers were available.

bufferTypeRequests.name: bufferTypeRequests
bufferTypeRequests.description: The number of times buffers of this type were requested.

bufferTypeMaximum.name: bufferTypeMaximum
bufferTypeMaximum.description: A high water mark for buffers of this type. This number represents the greatest number of buffers of this type ever allocated concurrently.

confReboot.name: confReboot
confReboot.description: The amount of time, in hundredths of a second, until the device reboots itself.

confCheckSum.name: confCheckSum
confCheckSum.description: Indicates the validity of the FastPath's configuration. If written to, allows the management station to flush the configuration (by setting invalid), or to protect it (by setting valid).

codeCheckSum.name: codeCheckSum
codeCheckSum.description: Indicates the validity of the FastPath's downloaded image. If written to, allows the management station to flush the downloaded image (by setting invalid), or to protect the it (by setting valid).

promVersion.name: promVersion
promVersion.description: The version number of the PROM multiplied by 100, for instance, PROM version 4.1 would return 410.

hwStatus.name: hwStatus
hwStatus.description: This integer is a bit mask which holds the following flags: 0x000001 - LocalTalk failed tests 0x000002 - Ethernet controller failed tests 0x000004 - FP4: The battery is low 0x000008 - Expansion RAM is present 0x000010 - FP4: Ethernet 12V Fuse blown 0x000020 - Expansion RAM failed tests 0x000040 - FP4: Disable Enet CRS jumper installed 0x000080 - FP4: Disable Enet SQE jumper installed 0x000100 - Software Jumper 1 installed 0x000200 - Software Jumper 2 installed 0x000400 - Software Jumper 3 installed 0x000800 - Software Jumper 4 installed 0x007000 - FP5: EtherModule type field 0x008000 - FP5: EtherModule type field is valid 0x010000 - FP5: RAM Bank 3 is present 0x020000 - FP5: RAM Bank 3 failed tests 0x040000 - FP5: RAM Bank 4 is present 0x080000 - FP5: RAM Bank 4 failed tests 0x100000 - FP5: Downloader mode 0x200000 - FP5: Software Jumper 5 installed 0x400000 - FP5: Hardware has LocalTalk IOP

confWhyReboot.name: confWhyReboot
confWhyReboot.description: Reason code for reboot scheduled by confReboot

confWhoReboot.name: confWhoReboot
confWhoReboot.description: Person responsible for reboot scheduled by confReboot

confRebootComment.name: confRebootComment
confRebootComment.description: Comment string for reboot scheduled by confReboot

confHowReboot.name: confHowReboot
confHowReboot.description: Action taken when reboot scheduled by confReboot occurs

tRTMPEntryTimeouts.name: tRTMPEntryTimeouts
tRTMPEntryTimeouts.description: The number of entries which were removed from routing table because the aging algorithm indicated that they were invalid.

tRTMPEntryDeletes.name: tRTMPEntryDeletes
tRTMPEntryDeletes.description: The number of entries which were removed from the routing table for any reason other than aging, for instance, due to a command from a Network Management station.

tRTMPEntryEqualReplaces.name: tRTMPEntryEqualReplaces
tRTMPEntryEqualReplaces.description: The number of entries whose route was replaced by another route with the same hop count.

tRTMPEntryBetterReplaces.name: tRTMPEntryBetterReplaces
tRTMPEntryBetterReplaces.description: The number of entries whose route was replaced by another route with a lower hop count.

tRTMPEntryAdds.name: tRTMPEntryAdds
tRTMPEntryAdds.description: The number of new entries which have been added to the table.

tRTMPZeroCounters.name: tRTMPZeroCounters
tRTMPZeroCounters.description: Writing this variable causes all the RTMP variables in this group to be set to zero.

tZIPDeletes.name: tZIPDeletes
tZIPDeletes.description: The number of Zones which have been deleted from the Zone Table.

tZIPAdds.name: tZIPAdds
tZIPAdds.description: The number of Zones which have been added to the Zone Table.

tZIPZeroCounters.name: tZIPZeroCounters
tZIPZeroCounters.description: Writing this variable causes all the ZIP variables in this group to be set to zero.

tAARPClearCache.name: tAARPClearCache
tAARPClearCache.description: Writing this variable clears the AARP Cache.

tKIPRoutesValid.name: tKIPRoutesValid
tKIPRoutesValid.description: This variable can be used to force KIP to reacquire its configuration information.

tARPClearCache.name: tARPClearCache
tARPClearCache.description: Writing this variable clears the ARP Cache.

tIPClearRoutingTable.name: tIPClearRoutingTable
tIPClearRoutingTable.description: Writing this variable clears the entire IP routing table.

tCommunityTrapHostType.name: tCommunityTrapHostType
tCommunityTrapHostType.description: This is the address family of the trap host. The Trap Host is the host to which the device sends all traps.

tCommunityTrapHostAddress.name: tCommunityTrapHostAddress
tCommunityTrapHostAddress.description: This is the Network Address of the host. It is interpreted according to the value of tCommunityTrapHostType.

tCommunitySetHostType.name: tCommunitySetHostType
tCommunitySetHostType.description: This is the address family of the set host. The Set Host is a host which is privileged to change any MIB variable.

tCommunitySetHostAddress.name: tCommunitySetHostAddress
tCommunitySetHostAddress.description: This is the Network Address of the Set Host. It is interpreted according to the value of tCommunityTrapHostType.

tCommunityList.name: tCommunityList
tCommunityList.description: The Communities Table describes the various communities known to the the device.

tCommunityEntry.name: tCommunityEntry
tCommunityEntry.description: The type of a row object in the community table. This represents a single SNMP Community. Community entries are indexed by counting integers starting with 1.

tCommunityAccess.name: tCommunityAccess
tCommunityAccess.description: This defines the privilege of the community. A 'read-only' community can examine any readable variable. A 'clear-statistics' community can reset non-critical counters. A 'configure' community has complete privileges. By setting the community access to 'no-access', a management station can deny all access by that community.

tEtherTable.name: tEtherTable
tEtherTable.description: Table of statistics for the ethernet interfaces of a device.

tEtherEntry.name: tEtherEntry
tEtherEntry.description: The type of a row object in the ethernet table. This represents a single Ethernet Interface. If an interface is not an Ethernet interface, there will not be a row in this table for that interface's value of ifIndex.

etherCRCErrors.name: etherCRCErrors
etherCRCErrors.description: The total number of CRC errors on this ethernet interface

etherAlignErrors.name: etherAlignErrors
etherAlignErrors.description: The total number of alignment errors on this ethernet interface.

etherResourceErrors.name: etherResourceErrors
etherResourceErrors.description: The total number of errors due to lack of resources on this ethernet interface.

etherOverrunErrors.name: etherOverrunErrors
etherOverrunErrors.description: The total number of overrun errors on this ethernet interface.

etherInPackets.name: etherInPackets

etherOutPackets.name: etherOutPackets
etherOutPackets.description: The total number of output packets on this ethernet interface.

etherBadTransmits.name: etherBadTransmits
etherBadTransmits.description: The total number of transmission errors on this ethernet interface.

etherOversizeFrames.name: etherOversizeFrames
etherOversizeFrames.description: The total number of oversize frame errors on this ethernet interface.

etherSpurRUReadys.name: etherSpurRUReadys
etherSpurRUReadys.description: The total number of spurious RU Ready interrupts on this ethernet interface.

etherSpurCUActives.name: etherSpurCUActives
etherSpurCUActives.description: The total number of spurious CU Active interrupts on this ethernet interface.

etherSpurUnknowns.name: etherSpurUnknowns
etherSpurUnknowns.description: The total number of unknown spurious interrupts on this ethernet interface.

etherBcastDrops.name: etherBcastDrops
etherBcastDrops.description: The total number of broadcast packets dropped to free resources on this ethernet interface.

etherReceiverRestarts.name: etherReceiverRestarts
etherReceiverRestarts.description: The total number of receiver restarts on this ethernet interface.

etherReinterrupts.name: etherReinterrupts
etherReinterrupts.description: The total number of reinterrupts on this ethernet interface.

etherBufferReroutes.name: etherBufferReroutes
etherBufferReroutes.description: The total number of buffers taken off of queues to service incoming packets on this ethernet interface.

etherBufferDrops.name: etherBufferDrops
etherBufferDrops.description: The total number of buffers dropped on this ethernet interface.

etherCollisions.name: etherCollisions
etherCollisions.description: The total number of collisions encountered on this ethernet interface.

etherDefers.name: etherDefers
etherDefers.description: The total number of deferrals encountered on this ethernet interface.

etherDMAUnderruns.name: etherDMAUnderruns
etherDMAUnderruns.description: The total number of DMA Underruns on this ethernet interface.

etherMaxCollisions.name: etherMaxCollisions
etherMaxCollisions.description: The total number of packets dropped on this ethernet interface because they encountered more than 16 collisions.

etherNoCarriers.name: etherNoCarriers
etherNoCarriers.description: The total number of no carrier errors experienced on this ethernet interface.

etherNoCTSs.name: etherNoCTSs
etherNoCTSs.description: The total number of no CTS errors experienced on this ethernet interface.

etherNoSQEs.name: etherNoSQEs
etherNoSQEs.description: The total number of no SQE errors experienced on this ethernet interface.
